text: Tiszakécske Futball Club is a Hungarian football club from the town of Tiszakécske, Hungary. ==History== Tiszakécske FC debuted in the 1997–98 season of the Hungarian League and finished fifteenth and were relegated. In 2018 Tiszakécske started to wear 2Rule sport kit.http://www.nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo_nb_ii/nb-ii-ket-masodosztalyu-csapat- is-2rule-ra-valtott-kepek-2651875 Tiszakécske were eliminated in the round of 16 of the 2018–19 Magyar Kupa by Budapest Honvéd FC on 1–2 aggregate. == Name Changes == *1993–1996: Tiszakécskei Futball Club *1996–1997: Tiszakécske FC- Eurobusz *1997–1999: Tiszakécske FC *1999: dissolved *2000: reestablished *2000–2011: Tiszakécskei VSE *2011–present: Tiszakécskei VSE-Andritz Kft. ==External links== * Profile ==References== Category:Football clubs in Hungary Category:2015 establishments in Hungary Category:Association football clubs established in 2015
